column5: Hey there,  I'm new to the board but have been watching it most days here and there.  Figured I'd post a few quick pics of some of the fish thus far....  Cheers
Welcome to the board!!  Looks like you enjoy fishing for the toothy ones.......nice pics!   Have yet to manage my first musky but one day!!
Nice fishies, Bud. Thanks for posting and welcome aboard!
Wow...that's quite a collection of toothy guys!  Welcome to the board...you'll find it's the best one around!  Looking forward to more of your reports.
Welcome! Looks like your having a good year so far. Enjoy your stay.  Cheers, 1leg
Welcome... great... another muskie dude.... next its fly fisherman, horse riders and sailboaters (all elitists in my book.... LOL)  Just kidding... welcome to the show..

Brian  I will e-mail you later.   Good to see you here it is a great site and you can pick up a lot of good info.  Being I don't get up there much anymore I will let you in on a few of my secret spots  Phil

Thanks everyone for the welcome.  I've followed the site for some time now and now that I finally have my own boat and hitting the water more than ever.  I fish mainly muskies but try out everything else as well.  It's been an up and down year thus far, I've landed one a few muskies myself this year, but have seen and lost quite a few more!  Quick note, that pickerel pictured above was 26" and was caught at 1pm trolling a 6 1/2" crankbait at 5.3MPH.  I doubt the walleye guys will believe me but it the truth, 20 FOW!  She hit liek a frieght train...we all thought she was a ski until her slowly rose up from beneath the boat!  Cheers to all!
Sounds like my first date with Monique.........

Welcome to the board.  Nice pics I believe you about the walleye.  I troll cranks for walleye alot on one of the lakes here although mostly in the evening and into the night and when they hit they really smack it.   Usuall long line troll big cranks as it gets dark and the walleye are up chasing ciscoes . Here is the pic of one my brother in law got with me a couple weeks ago

welcome this is a great board for fish talk ! some nice fish you have caught there im heading up to nipissing for 10 days in 2 days for some fishing and i hope to catch my first muskie!!!!!!! cheers little angler
Welcome, you've come to the right place   Those are some nice fish, I look forward to your future reports  Maureen
Welcome aboard Muskiewannabe.  Some nice looking fish there.  You'll love it here and the people you will meet from this board are a fantastic bunch.  Joey
